By Chibuike
Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Hon. Kingsley Chinda has emerged the House Minority Leader as the Peoples Democratic Party on Wednesday announced its principal minority officers as stipulated by law. The party’s decision was contained in a letter dated June 26,
2019, and addressed to the Speaker, Femi Gbajabiamila. Other positions announced were Chukwuka Onyema, Deputy Minority Leader; Yakubu Barde, Minority Whip; and Muraina Ajibola, Deputy Minority Whip. The letter signed by Secondus partly read; “in accordance with
extant laws, House rules, conventions and general legislative practices
worldwide, the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) after wide consultations with
house caucus, the party leadership from the geopolitical zones and the National
Working Committee (NWC) hereby forward the names of the duly agreed and
approved House Minority leadership.” Sundiata Post recalls that a similar letter from the party was
red at the flow of the senate by the Senate President, Ahmed Lawan, and Senator
Enyinnaya Abaribe was unveiled as Minority Leader of the senate.